00001 *DECK DQAGP
00002       SUBROUTINE DQAGP (F, A, B, NPTS2, POINTS, EPSABS, EPSREL, RESULT,
00003      +   ABSERR, NEVAL, IER, LENIW, LENW, LAST, IWORK, WORK)
00004 C***BEGIN PROLOGUE  DQAGP
00005 C***PURPOSE  The routine calculates an approximation result to a given
00006 C            definite integral I = Integral of F over (A,B),
00007 C            hopefully satisfying following claim for accuracy
00008 C            break points of the integration interval, where local
00009 C            difficulties of the integrand may occur (e.g.
00010 C            SINGULARITIES, DISCONTINUITIES), are provided by the user.
00011 C***LIBRARY   SLATEC (QUADPACK)
00012 C***CATEGORY  H2A2A1
00013 C***TYPE      DOUBLE PRECISION (QAGP-S, DQAGP-D)
00014 C***KEYWORDS  AUTOMATIC INTEGRATOR, EXTRAPOLATION, GENERAL-PURPOSE,
00015 C             GLOBALLY ADAPTIVE, QUADPACK, QUADRATURE,
00016 C             SINGULARITIES AT USER SPECIFIED POINTS
00017 C***AUTHOR  Piessens, Robert
00018 C             Applied Mathematics and Programming Division
00019 C             K. U. Leuven
00020 C           de Doncker, Elise
00021 C             Applied Mathematics and Programming Division
00022 C             K. U. Leuven
00023 C***DESCRIPTION
00024 C
00025 C        Computation of a definite integral
00026 C        Standard fortran subroutine
00027 C        Double precision version
00028 C
00029 C        PARAMETERS
00030 C         ON ENTRY
00031 C            F      - Double precision
00032 C                     Function subprogram defining the integrand
00033 C                     Function F(X). The actual name for F needs to be
00034 C                     declared E X T E R N A L in the driver program.
00035 C
00036 C            A      - Double precision
00037 C                     Lower limit of integration
00038 C
00039 C            B      - Double precision
00040 C                     Upper limit of integration
00041 C
00042 C            NPTS2  - Integer
00043 C                     Number equal to two more than the number of
00044 C                     user-supplied break points within the integration
00045 C                     range, NPTS.GE.2.
00046 C                     If NPTS2.LT.2, The routine will end with IER = 6.
00047 C
00048 C            POINTS - Double precision
00049 C                     Vector of dimension NPTS2, the first (NPTS2-2)
00050 C                     elements of which are the user provided break
00051 C                     points. If these points do not constitute an
00052 C                     ascending sequence there will be an automatic
00053 C                     sorting.
00054 C
00055 C            EPSABS - Double precision
00056 C                     Absolute accuracy requested
00057 C            EPSREL - Double precision
00058 C                     Relative accuracy requested
00059 C                     If  EPSABS.LE.0
00060 C                     And EPSREL.LT.MAX(50*REL.MACH.ACC.,0.5D-28),
00061 C                     The routine will end with IER = 6.
00062 C
00063 C         ON RETURN
00064 C            RESULT - Double precision
00065 C                     Approximation to the integral
00066 C
00067 C            ABSERR - Double precision
00068 C                     Estimate of the modulus of the absolute error,
00069 C                     which should equal or exceed ABS(I-RESULT)
00070 C
00071 C            NEVAL  - Integer
00072 C                     Number of integrand evaluations
00073 C
00074 C            IER    - Integer
00075 C                     IER = 0 Normal and reliable termination of the
00076 C                             routine. It is assumed that the requested
00077 C                             accuracy has been achieved.
00078 C                     IER.GT.0 Abnormal termination of the routine.
00079 C                             The estimates for integral and error are
00080 C                             less reliable. it is assumed that the
00081 C                             requested accuracy has not been achieved.
00082 C            ERROR MESSAGES
00083 C                     IER = 1 Maximum number of subdivisions allowed
00084 C                             has been achieved. one can allow more
00085 C                             subdivisions by increasing the value of
00086 C                             LIMIT (and taking the according dimension
00087 C                             adjustments into account). However, if
00088 C                             this yields no improvement it is advised
00089 C                             to analyze the integrand in order to
00090 C                             determine the integration difficulties. If
00091 C                             the position of a local difficulty can be
00092 C                             determined (i.e. SINGULARITY,
00093 C                             DISCONTINUITY within the interval), it
00094 C                             should be supplied to the routine as an
00095 C                             element of the vector points. If necessary
00096 C                             an appropriate special-purpose integrator
00097 C                             must be used, which is designed for
00098 C                             handling the type of difficulty involved.
00099 C                         = 2 The occurrence of roundoff error is
00100 C                             detected, which prevents the requested
00101 C                             tolerance from being achieved.
00102 C                             The error may be under-estimated.
00103 C                         = 3 Extremely bad integrand behaviour occurs
00104 C                             at some points of the integration
00105 C                             interval.
00106 C                         = 4 The algorithm does not converge.
00107 C                             roundoff error is detected in the
00108 C                             extrapolation table.
00109 C                             It is presumed that the requested
00110 C                             tolerance cannot be achieved, and that
00111 C                             the returned RESULT is the best which
00112 C                             can be obtained.
00113 C                         = 5 The integral is probably divergent, or
00114 C                             slowly convergent. it must be noted that
00115 C                             divergence can occur with any other value
00116 C                             of IER.GT.0.
00117 C                         = 6 The input is invalid because
00118 C                             NPTS2.LT.2 or
00119 C                             break points are specified outside
00120 C                             the integration range or
00121 C                             (EPSABS.LE.0 and
00122 C                              EPSREL.LT.MAX(50*REL.MACH.ACC.,0.5D-28))
00123 C                             RESULT, ABSERR, NEVAL, LAST are set to
00124 C                             zero.  Except when LENIW or LENW or NPTS2
00125 C                             is invalid, IWORK(1), IWORK(LIMIT+1),
00126 C                             WORK(LIMIT*2+1) and WORK(LIMIT*3+1)
00127 C                             are set to zero.
00128 C                             WORK(1) is set to A and WORK(LIMIT+1)
00129 C                             to B (where LIMIT = (LENIW-NPTS2)/2).
00130 C
00131 C         DIMENSIONING PARAMETERS
00132 C            LENIW - Integer
00133 C                    Dimensioning parameter for IWORK
00134 C                    LENIW determines LIMIT = (LENIW-NPTS2)/2,
00135 C                    which is the maximum number of subintervals in the
00136 C                    partition of the given integration interval (A,B),
00137 C                    LENIW.GE.(3*NPTS2-2).
00138 C                    If LENIW.LT.(3*NPTS2-2), the routine will end with
00139 C                    IER = 6.
00140 C
00141 C            LENW  - Integer
00142 C                    Dimensioning parameter for WORK
00143 C                    LENW must be at least LENIW*2-NPTS2.
00144 C                    If LENW.LT.LENIW*2-NPTS2, the routine will end
00145 C                    with IER = 6.
00146 C
00147 C            LAST  - Integer
00148 C                    On return, LAST equals the number of subintervals
00149 C                    produced in the subdivision process, which
00150 C                    determines the number of significant elements
00151 C                    actually in the WORK ARRAYS.
00152 C
00153 C         WORK ARRAYS
00154 C            IWORK - Integer
00155 C                    Vector of dimension at least LENIW. on return,
00156 C                    the first K elements of which contain
00157 C                    pointers to the error estimates over the
00158 C                    subintervals, such that WORK(LIMIT*3+IWORK(1)),...,
00159 C                    WORK(LIMIT*3+IWORK(K)) form a decreasing
00160 C                    sequence, with K = LAST if LAST.LE.(LIMIT/2+2), and
00161 C                    K = LIMIT+1-LAST otherwise
00162 C                    IWORK(LIMIT+1), ...,IWORK(LIMIT+LAST) Contain the
00163 C                     subdivision levels of the subintervals, i.e.
00164 C                     if (AA,BB) is a subinterval of (P1,P2)
00165 C                     where P1 as well as P2 is a user-provided
00166 C                     break point or integration LIMIT, then (AA,BB) has
00167 C                     level L if ABS(BB-AA) = ABS(P2-P1)*2**(-L),
00168 C                    IWORK(LIMIT*2+1), ..., IWORK(LIMIT*2+NPTS2) have
00169 C                     no significance for the user,
00170 C                    note that LIMIT = (LENIW-NPTS2)/2.
00171 C
00172 C            WORK  - Double precision
00173 C                    Vector of dimension at least LENW
00174 C                    on return
00175 C                    WORK(1), ..., WORK(LAST) contain the left
00176 C                     end points of the subintervals in the
00177 C                     partition of (A,B),
00178 C                    WORK(LIMIT+1), ..., WORK(LIMIT+LAST) contain
00179 C                     the right end points,
00180 C                    WORK(LIMIT*2+1), ..., WORK(LIMIT*2+LAST) contain
00181 C                     the integral approximations over the subintervals,
00182 C                    WORK(LIMIT*3+1), ..., WORK(LIMIT*3+LAST)
00183 C                     contain the corresponding error estimates,
00184 C                    WORK(LIMIT*4+1), ..., WORK(LIMIT*4+NPTS2)
00185 C                     contain the integration limits and the
00186 C                     break points sorted in an ascending sequence.
00187 C                    note that LIMIT = (LENIW-NPTS2)/2.
00188 C
00189 C***REFERENCES  (NONE)
00190 C***ROUTINES CALLED  DQAGPE, XERMSG
00191 C***REVISION HISTORY  (YYMMDD)
00192 C   800101  DATE WRITTEN
00193 C   890831  Modified array declarations.  (WRB)
00194 C   890831  REVISION DATE from Version 3.2
00195 C   891214  Prologue converted to Version 4.0 format.  (BAB)
00196 C   900315  CALLs to XERROR changed to CALLs to XERMSG.  (THJ)
00197 C***END PROLOGUE  DQAGP
00198 C
00199       DOUBLE PRECISION A,ABSERR,B,EPSABS,EPSREL,F,POINTS,RESULT,WORK
00200       INTEGER IER,IWORK,LAST,LENIW,LENW,LIMIT,LVL,L1,L2,L3,L4,NEVAL,
00201      1  NPTS2
00202 C
00203       DIMENSION IWORK(*),POINTS(*),WORK(*)
00204 C
00205       EXTERNAL F
00206 C
00207 C         CHECK VALIDITY OF LIMIT AND LENW.
00208 C
00209 C***FIRST EXECUTABLE STATEMENT  DQAGP
00210       IER = 6
00211       NEVAL = 0
00212       LAST = 0
00213       RESULT = 0.0D+00
00214       ABSERR = 0.0D+00
00215       IF(LENIW.LT.(3*NPTS2-2).OR.LENW.LT.(LENIW*2-NPTS2).OR.NPTS2.LT.2)
00216      1  GO TO 10
00217 C
00218 C         PREPARE CALL FOR DQAGPE.
00219 C
00220       LIMIT = (LENIW-NPTS2)/2
00221       L1 = LIMIT+1
00222       L2 = LIMIT+L1
00223       L3 = LIMIT+L2
00224       L4 = LIMIT+L3
00225 C
00226       CALL DQAGPE(F,A,B,NPTS2,POINTS,EPSABS,EPSREL,LIMIT,RESULT,ABSERR,
00227      1  NEVAL,IER,WORK(1),WORK(L1),WORK(L2),WORK(L3),WORK(L4),
00228      2  IWORK(1),IWORK(L1),IWORK(L2),LAST)
00229 C
00230 C         CALL ERROR HANDLER IF NECESSARY.
00231 C
00232       LVL = 0
00233 10    IF(IER.EQ.6) LVL = 1
00234       IF (IER .NE. 0) CALL XERMSG ('SLATEC', 'DQAGP',
00235      +   'ABNORMAL RETURN', IER, LVL)
00236       RETURN
00237       END
